{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01AbWAP4pzMsxrFdVQpc6rBg","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here's the full content of the lordofrngs test file:\n\n## Test File Overview\n\n**Location**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/tests/lordofrngs.ts`\n\nThe test file is comprehensive with **1,099 lines** covering the full lordofrngs game flow. Here are the key patterns and helpers:\n\n### Core Imports & Constants\n- Uses **mocha** (describe/it) + **chai** (expect) for assertions\n- **anchor-bankrun** for local blockchain simulation\n- IDL dynamically loaded from compiled output at runtime\n- Three key constants: `TIER_IRON`, `TIER_IRON_AMOUNT` (5M lamports), `COUNTDOWN_SECONDS` (60)\n- `TOTAL_FEE_BPS` (300 = 3%) and `RESOLVE_TIMEOUT_SECONDS` (120)\n\n### Test Context Factory (Lines 70-133)\n```typescript\ninterface TestContext {\n  context: Awaited<ReturnType<typeof startAnchor>>;\n  creator: PublicKey;\n  treasury: Keypair;\n  creatorProgram: Program<Lordofrngs>;\n  configPda: PublicKey;\n  player2: Keypair;\n  player2Program: Program<Lordofrngs>;\n  mockRandomness: Keypair;\n  mockOraoProgram: Keypair;\n  mockOraoNetworkState: Keypair;\n  mockOraoTreasury: Keypair;\n}\n```\n\nCreates pre-funded accounts for testing, including mock Orao VRF accounts.\n\n### PDA Helpers (Lines 39-56)\n- `getConfigPda()` — \"lord_config\" seed\n- `getRoundPda(tier, roundNumber)` — \"jackpot_round\" + tier byte + round u64 LE\n\n### Randomness & Payout Helpers (Lines 257-327)\n- `setMockRandomness(t, data)` — Sets account data on mock VRF account\n- `buildRandomness(winningSlot, totalEntries)` — Creates 32-byte buffer where first u64 LE mod totalEntries yields winning slot\n- `deriveWinner(randomness, totalEntries, players)` — Mirrors on-chain logic to determine winner from randomness\n- `getBalance(t, pubkey)` — Fetches lamports balance\n\n### Instruction Helpers (Lines 154-358)\n- `initConfig(t)` — initialize_config instruction\n- `createRound(t, tier, roundNumber, numEntries, creator?)` — create_round instruction\n- `joinRound(program, player, configPda, tier, roundNumber, numEntries)` — join_round instruction\n- `buyMoreEntries(program, player, configPda, tier, roundNumber, numEntries)` — buy_more_entries instruction\n- `startSpin(program, caller, t, tier, roundNumber)` — start_spin instruction (with VRF accounts)\n- `claimPayout(program, caller, t, winnerAccount, tier, roundNumber)` — claim_payout instruction\n- `timeoutRefund(program, caller, t, playerAccounts, tier, roundNumber)` — timeout_refund instruction with remaining accounts array\n\n### Clock Warping (Lines 138-149 & 360-372)\n- `warpPastCountdown(t)` — Advances clock by 200 slots + 70 seconds (past 60s countdown)\n- `warpPastResolveDeadline(t)` — Advances clock by 400 slots + 180 seconds (past countdown + resolve deadline)\n\n### Test Suites (Lines 377-1098)\n\n1. **initialize_config** — Verifies config creation, authority, treasury, paused=false, roundCounters=[0,0,0,0,0,0]\n2. **create_round** — Tests PDA creation, escrow balance calculation, counter increments, tier validation, zero entries rejection\n3. **join_round** — Tests second player triggers Active phase, phase transition, duplicate player rejection, 20-player max, multiple entries\n4. **buy_more_entries** — Tests entry count updates, escrow updates, phase constraints, non-player rejection\n5. **start_spin** — Tests Waiting→Active→Locked transition, countdown expiration check, idempotency, phase validation\n6. **claim_payout** — Tests winner derivation, fee calculation, payout distribution, PDA closure, randomness fulfillment check, wrong winner rejection, phase validation\n7. **timeout_refund** — Tests refund after timeout, proportional refunds, fulfilled VRF rejection, timeout elapsed check, phase validation\n\nAll test patterns demonstrate bankrun testing conventions, proper mock account setup, and comprehensive balance/state verification."},{"type