{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01SpzEJLzvWvDAjY3bEhE4dK","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now let me compile the complete findings. Based on my search, I found the `force_close` instruction in the coinflip program. Here are all the relevant files and code:\n\n## Search Results Summary\n\n### Found in Coinflip Program: **YES**\n\n**Location**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/programs/coinflip/`\n\n### All Relevant Code\n\n**1. Main Program Entry Point** (`lib.rs`):\n```rust\npub fn force_close(ctx: Context<ForceClose>) -> Result<()> {\n    instructions::force_close::handler(ctx)\n}\n```\n\n**2. Instruction Module Export** (`instructions/mod.rs`):\n```rust\npub mod force_close;\npub use force_close::*;\n```\n\n**3. Complete Force Close Implementation** (`instructions/force_close.rs`):\n```rust\nuse anchor_lang::prelude::*;\n\nuse crate::state::CoinflipConfig;\n\n/// Admin-only instruction to close a match account that can't be deserialized\n/// (e.g., after an account layout migration). Drains all lamports to the\n/// original creator and zeroes the account data.\n#[derive(Accounts)]\npub struct ForceClose<'info> {\n    /// Config authority (admin).\n    pub authority: Signer<'info>,\n\n    /// The config PDA — validates authority.\n    #[account(\n        seeds = [b\"coinflip_config\"],\n        bump = config.bump,\n        has_one = authority,\n    )]\n    pub config: Account<'info, CoinflipConfig>,\n\n    /// CHECK: The match account to close. Not deserialized — may have old layout.\n    #[account(mut)]\n    pub match_account: AccountInfo<'info>,\n\n    /// CHECK: Receives the lamports. Should be the match creator or admin.\n    #[account(mut)]\n    pub recipient: AccountInfo<'info>,\n}\n\npub fn handler(ctx: Context<ForceClose>) -> Result<()> {\n    let match_info = &ctx.accounts.match_account;\n\n    // Verify it's owned by this program\n    require_keys_eq!(*match_info.owner, crate::ID);\n\n    // Drain all lamports to recipient\n    let lamports = match_info.lamports();\n    **match_info.try_borrow_mut_lamports()? -= lamports;\n    **ctx.accounts.recipient.try_borrow_mut_lamports()? += lamports;\n\n    // Zero the data so the account is effectively closed\n    match_info.try_borrow_mut_data()?.fill(0);\n\n    Ok(())\n}\n```\n\n### Found in Shared Crate: **NO**\n\nNo occurrences of `force_close`, `forceClose`, or `force_settle` were found in `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/shared/src/`.\n\n### Summary\n\nThe `force_close` instruction is an **admin-only** operation designed to handle emergency closure of match accounts that cannot be deserialized (e.g., after account layout migrations). It:\n- Requires the config authority signature\n- Does not deserialize the match account (allowing it to work with corrupted/old account layouts)\n- Drains all lamports to a specified recipient\n- Zeros out the account data\n\nThere is no `force_settle` instruction and no such code in the shared crate."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: ae423d3 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 32255\ntool_uses: 10\nduration_ms: 23838</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cd70fe61-545b-465a-ae36-fc0d70c24914","uuid":"a4c7e656-6964-456d-8cff-a32175c7cc90","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Search for any \"force_close\" or \"forceClose\" or \"force_settle\" instruction in the coinflip program at /workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/programs/coinflip/. Read any matching files fully. Also check if there's a force_close in the shared crate at /workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/shared/src/. Return ALL relevant code.","agentId":"ae423d3","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now let me compile the complete findings. Based on my search, I found the `force_close` instruction in the coinflip program. Here are all the relevant files and code:\n\n## Search